===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} {{term|bere|lang=en}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|beor|bēor|lang=ang}}, akin to Old Saxon {{term|bior}}, Old High German {{term|bior|lang=goh}}, Middle Low German & Middle Dutch {{term|ber|bēr||beer}}, Old Norse {{term|bjōrr||beer|lang=non}} (probably from Old English {{term|beor|bēor|lang=ang}}); Dutch & German {{term|Bier||beer}}, Frisian {{term|biar||beer}}. Possibly related to Old English {{term|brēowan||to brew|lang=ang}} and {{term|beorma||yeast, head of a beer|lang=ang}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/bɪə/}}, {{SAMPA|/bI@/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/biɹ/|/bɪɹ/}}, {{SAMPA|/bir/|/bIr/}}
* {{audio|en-us-beer.ogg|Audio (US)}}
